cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of human pose estimation. The use of attention modules and multi-resolution networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed modifications to the keypoint regressor and the use of fine-to-coarse connections suggest that it could also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
